WEBVTT

00:04.559 --> 00:07.502
[gentle music]

00:07.602 --> 00:14.449
♪ ♪

00:19.814 --> 00:22.437
[relaxed music]

00:22.537 --> 00:24.840
[camera shutters clicking]

00:24.940 --> 00:27.782
[indistinct chatter]

00:30.385 --> 00:32.167
[elevator dings]

00:32.267 --> 00:34.970
- Hey.

00:35.070 --> 00:37.893
First of all, whoa.

00:37.993 --> 00:39.815
Secondly, why didn't you
tell me?

00:39.915 --> 00:41.176
- I did--I did try to tell you.

00:41.276 --> 00:42.818
I called you right after

00:42.918 --> 00:44.499
Danny Michael Davis
dropped this on me.

00:44.599 --> 00:46.381
You weren't really listening.
- I thought I was listening.

00:46.481 --> 00:48.143
You said that there
was a problem with the Chirp,

00:48.243 --> 00:51.026
so I assumed that
it was a coding issue, not a...

00:51.126 --> 00:52.547
that issue.

00:52.647 --> 00:55.190
- Well, when a Black employee
tells you

00:55.290 --> 00:56.832
that a tech device
is having trouble

00:56.932 --> 00:58.874
recognizing people of color,

00:58.974 --> 01:01.697
I think you'd be able
to put two and two together.

01:02.938 --> 01:04.960
- You are right.
Uh...

01:05.060 --> 01:07.162
Right, I'm sorry.

01:07.262 --> 01:11.006
I was so focused on coming up
with a solution,

01:11.106 --> 01:13.248
I wasn't hearing
what was behind the problem.

01:13.348 --> 01:14.650
- Well, now you know,

01:14.750 --> 01:16.051
and now I need
to process the fact

01:16.151 --> 01:17.653
that I just publicly
called out my own company

01:17.753 --> 01:18.894
as its spokesperson

01:18.994 --> 01:20.736
to every major
news media outlet

01:20.836 --> 01:22.978
in Silicon Valley.

01:23.078 --> 01:24.820
[sighs]
[elevator dings]

01:24.920 --> 01:31.807
♪ ♪

01:35.290 --> 01:37.273
- And then Simon was like,

01:37.373 --> 01:40.676
"The Chirp doesn't recognize
Black people

01:40.776 --> 01:44.159
because Sprqpoint doesn't
recognize Black people."

01:44.259 --> 01:45.841
- Honestly, I am proud of him.

01:45.941 --> 01:47.923
Also, I'm here for this tea
that you are spilling

01:48.023 --> 01:50.406
which makes me want
my man, Earl Grey.

01:50.506 --> 01:51.687
And a man.

01:51.787 --> 01:53.008
A tall man.

01:53.108 --> 01:54.410
- You deserve it.

01:54.510 --> 01:56.252
- Wow, you know,
it really takes guts

01:56.352 --> 01:57.693
speaking truth to power
like that.

01:57.793 --> 02:00.256
- Yeah, I'm proud of him.

02:00.356 --> 02:03.499
Although I do feel like
a little bit of an idiot

02:03.599 --> 02:05.701
because he did try to tell me

02:05.801 --> 02:06.982
there was more to the problem
with The Chirp,

02:07.082 --> 02:09.625
and I just wasn't hearing him.
[sighs]

02:09.725 --> 02:11.787
The PSA is right, you know?
Don't do drugs.

02:11.887 --> 02:12.908
- Wait, you did drugs?

02:13.008 --> 02:14.590
- And I may or may not have

02:14.690 --> 02:16.472
done them with the CEO
of Sprqpoint.

02:16.572 --> 02:18.034
- Danny Michael Davis
gave you drugs?

02:18.134 --> 02:19.355
- Actually, I gave him drugs.
[cell phone buzzes]

02:19.455 --> 02:20.556
Don't ask.

02:20.656 --> 02:21.517
And now he texts me
all the time.

02:21.617 --> 02:22.798
He thinks we're besties.

02:22.898 --> 02:24.680
Oh, he's texting me
right this second!

02:24.780 --> 02:26.522
He's spiraling so bad
about Simon's press conference,

02:26.622 --> 02:28.084
he just bought a private jet

02:28.184 --> 02:29.325
for the African
Children's Choir.

02:29.425 --> 02:30.606
- Oh, boy.
- Honestly, Max,

02:30.706 --> 02:32.608
we should hit him up
to invest in the company.

02:32.708 --> 02:34.450
I mean, there's no one easier
to shake down

02:34.550 --> 02:35.972
than a well-intended
billionaire

02:36.072 --> 02:37.333
with white guilt.
- I don't know.

02:37.433 --> 02:39.775
Do we really want to start
our company with guilt money?

02:39.875 --> 02:41.577
- Mm, it's better
than no money.

02:41.677 --> 02:43.699
Last time I checked, we didn't
have a plethora of options.

02:43.799 --> 02:45.261
- It's not a terrible idea.

02:45.361 --> 02:46.582
He's clearly
in the donating mood,

02:46.682 --> 02:49.265
and I would say
that your business

02:49.365 --> 02:51.067
pretty much embodies everything
he's feeling guilty about.

02:51.167 --> 02:52.348
- How could he refuse us?

02:52.448 --> 02:53.990
Honestly, I dare him
to refuse us.

02:54.090 --> 02:56.032
- Come on,
we can't pitch the founder

02:56.132 --> 02:57.673
of one of the largest
tech companies in the world

02:57.773 --> 03:00.036
our scrappy little spin
on dining out.

03:00.136 --> 03:02.118
[notification swoops]
- Ah, but you can, mm-hmm.

03:02.218 --> 03:03.519
You guys are on Danny's
calendar tomorrow

03:03.619 --> 03:05.722
from 11:12 to 11:17.
- Are you serious? What?

03:05.822 --> 03:07.043
That was fast.

03:07.143 --> 03:08.725
- Ah, sweet, sweet
secondhand privilege.

03:08.825 --> 03:10.446
- I told you we're besties.

03:10.546 --> 03:12.729
- Okay, yeah, we can do this
in only five minutes.

03:12.829 --> 03:15.091
- Honey, we can do anything
in any amount of minutes.

03:15.191 --> 03:16.853
We just need to get
that rich man to listen to us.

03:16.953 --> 03:18.615
- Listen.

03:18.715 --> 03:20.617
You're right.

03:20.717 --> 03:23.339
That's exactly what I need
to start doing more of.

03:23.439 --> 03:24.621
Listening.

03:24.721 --> 03:27.584
[upbeat music]

03:27.684 --> 03:30.707
Hey, hey.

03:30.807 --> 03:32.709
I thought a lot
about what you said,

03:32.809 --> 03:35.992
and I know that I can't change
all of Sprqpoint,

03:36.092 --> 03:37.193
but I can try and help
make things better

03:37.293 --> 03:38.755
on the fourth floor.

03:38.855 --> 03:41.317
So instead of waiting for
the higher-ups to do something,

03:41.417 --> 03:44.200
I came up with my own
great plan.

03:44.300 --> 03:45.522
Town hall

03:45.622 --> 03:47.163
where participation
is not mandatory--

03:47.263 --> 03:48.204
- But strongly encouraged.

03:48.304 --> 03:49.806
Yeah, I got your Slack messages

03:49.906 --> 03:52.208
and your barrage
of Insta Stories.

03:52.308 --> 03:55.612
Um, are you sure
this is the best approach?

03:55.712 --> 03:57.574
- You rightly pointed out
that I wasn't listening...

03:57.674 --> 03:58.655
- Mm-hmm.

03:58.755 --> 04:00.937
- So we are going to listen

04:01.037 --> 04:03.039
for as long as it takes.

04:04.120 --> 04:06.423
Good morning, everyone!

04:06.523 --> 04:08.665
Thanks to Simon's

04:08.765 --> 04:11.788
brave call to action yesterday,

04:11.888 --> 04:15.071
I organized this town hall

04:15.171 --> 04:17.314
