12:56.657 --> 12:59.159
just left a little meeting
with some of the board,

12:59.259 --> 13:01.041
and they were just requesting
that Simon just...

13:01.141 --> 13:02.322
[mimics squelch]
You know?

13:02.422 --> 13:03.964
Retract everything he expressed

13:04.064 --> 13:06.066
at the press conference.

13:06.827 --> 13:08.088
- Retract?

13:08.188 --> 13:10.010
- He just needs to say
that it was his opinion,

13:10.110 --> 13:12.412
you know, and, um,

13:12.512 --> 13:15.255
that, uh,
just his opinion alone

13:15.355 --> 13:16.937
and doesn't represent
the larger experience

13:17.037 --> 13:18.378
of being an employee
at Sprqpoint.

13:18.478 --> 13:19.660
You know, so we don't get sued.

13:19.760 --> 13:20.981
- That sounds...

13:21.081 --> 13:22.463
- Yeah, yes, yes.

13:22.563 --> 13:25.305
That is terrible, unfair,

13:25.405 --> 13:28.268
hella dumb,
but look, you know,

13:28.368 --> 13:31.271
as a CEO, I gotta do stuff
that's not easy sometimes,

13:31.371 --> 13:34.715
and that forces me to have
the tough conversations,

13:34.815 --> 13:35.996
which is why I'm gonna
have you do it.

13:36.096 --> 13:37.278
- I'm sorry.

13:37.378 --> 13:39.360
You want me to be one

13:39.460 --> 13:40.441
to talk to Simon about this?

13:40.541 --> 13:42.363
- Oh, great.
Same page.

13:42.463 --> 13:43.924
I feel so much better
about this already.

13:44.024 --> 13:45.926
- No, Danny,
I don't think I should.

13:46.026 --> 13:48.809
- Zoey, you are his supervisor,

13:48.909 --> 13:51.492
and we both know
it's gonna sound a lot better

13:51.592 --> 13:53.374
coming from a mouth
that isn't mine.

13:53.474 --> 13:55.136
Oh, God.

13:55.236 --> 13:57.498
Another board member's yacht
just docked.

13:57.598 --> 14:00.461
I gotta go meet Artemis
down by the Wharf.

14:00.561 --> 14:03.824
Somebody bring me my boat shoes
and a Dramamine!

14:03.924 --> 14:05.926
[quirky music]

14:08.128 --> 14:11.032
[quirky music]

14:11.132 --> 14:13.914
- [sighs]

14:14.014 --> 14:15.916
Hey, guys.

14:16.016 --> 14:17.918
- Oh, snap.

14:18.018 --> 14:19.600
Look what the cat dragged in.

14:19.700 --> 14:20.841
- Who's this thirst trap?

14:20.941 --> 14:22.643
- That's Max.
He used to work at that desk.

14:22.743 --> 14:24.045
He was the one who was secretly
in love with Zoey,

14:24.145 --> 14:26.447
but everyone knew it.
- Okay.

14:26.547 --> 14:27.929
A couple of you guys
are "office hot,"

14:28.029 --> 14:29.410
but I think he may
be "real world hot."

14:29.510 --> 14:30.611
- That's hurtful.

14:30.711 --> 14:31.672
Everyone knows
I'm a San Francisco seven.

14:31.752 --> 14:33.014
- Hey, Max.

14:33.114 --> 14:34.295
- Hey, Leif.

14:34.395 --> 14:35.696
- Did you get any of my texts

14:35.796 --> 14:37.178
or that Edible Arrangement
I sent?

14:37.278 --> 14:39.100
I just feel terrible
about getting you fired.

14:39.200 --> 14:40.942
- Weirdly,
not as bad as I felt,

14:41.042 --> 14:43.424
but it's all good now because
I just got Danny Michael Davis

14:43.524 --> 14:44.745
to fund my new concept,

14:44.845 --> 14:46.387
and I wanted to run
some tech stuff by Gabe.

14:46.487 --> 14:47.668
Where is Gabe?

14:47.768 --> 14:49.791
- Um, he got transferred
to floor five.

14:49.891 --> 14:51.953
- And Jared?
- Also to five.

14:52.053 --> 14:53.354
- Oh.

14:53.454 --> 14:56.317
- Hey, um, do you wanna
run it by us?

14:56.417 --> 14:58.419
- You can sit right here, boo.

14:59.660 --> 15:01.442
- I guess if you guys
don't mind, sure.

15:01.542 --> 15:03.204
- Yes.
All right, cool.

15:03.304 --> 15:05.847
- So, um, the scheduling tab
isn't fully syncing

15:05.947 --> 15:07.208
with all the food delivery
apps.

15:07.308 --> 15:08.850
- Okay.

15:08.950 --> 15:11.252
Okay, yeah,
I actually don't hate this.

15:11.352 --> 15:14.095
Decent layout, sexy banner.
Did you do all this yourself?

15:14.195 --> 15:15.336
- Yeah, turns out
when I'm not constantly

15:15.436 --> 15:16.618
being judged by my peers,

15:16.718 --> 15:18.139
I have a smidge of talent
in this arena.

15:18.239 --> 15:21.382
- Well, we can help you
get this sorted out real quick.

15:21.482 --> 15:23.464
- Uh...

15:23.564 --> 15:26.067
- I mean, if you want us to.

15:26.167 --> 15:27.989
- Still know how to use
this little lady?

15:28.089 --> 15:29.871
♪ ♪

15:29.971 --> 15:31.793
- Hell yeah.

15:31.893 --> 15:33.434
Let's do this.

15:33.534 --> 15:36.438
[indistinct chatter]

15:36.538 --> 15:39.761
♪ ♪

15:39.861 --> 15:41.563
- Hey, Mo.

15:41.663 --> 15:43.284
How's the pitch?

15:43.384 --> 15:44.486
- Amazing.

15:44.586 --> 15:46.167
Danny is going to invest
in the business.

15:46.267 --> 15:47.489
- That's great.

15:47.589 --> 15:49.451
Um, actually,

15:49.551 --> 15:50.772
I'm in a little bit
of a pickle,

15:50.872 --> 15:51.793
and I thought you'd
be the perfect person

15:51.873 --> 15:53.174
to talk to about this.

15:53.274 --> 15:55.056
- Oh, darling, I get that.
My voice is so soothing.

15:55.156 --> 15:58.059
- Uh, Danny Michael Davis

15:58.159 --> 16:00.862
told me that the board
needs Simon

16:00.962 --> 16:03.345
to retract everything he said
at the press conference,

16:03.445 --> 16:05.026
and he wants me to tell him,

16:05.126 --> 16:08.510
and I don't want it to sound...

16:08.610 --> 16:10.151
weird,

16:10.251 --> 16:11.833
and I also want him to know
that I have his back.

16:11.933 --> 16:14.876
So how would you say it?

16:14.976 --> 16:16.958
I mean, if you were me.

16:17.058 --> 16:19.201
- I know you're not
asking your Black friend

16:19.301 --> 16:20.642
how to talk to your other
Black friend.

16:20.742 --> 16:21.923
- No.

16:22.023 --> 16:27.769
I mean, yes, but I just--

16:27.869 --> 16:30.852
I...um...

16:30.952 --> 16:32.574
I thought that you could
offer some guidance

16:32.674 --> 16:34.136
since you're--
- Black?

16:34.236 --> 16:36.098
- No.

16:36.198 --> 16:37.499
Insightful?

16:37.599 --> 16:40.382
[Mary J. Blige's
"No More Drama"]

16:40.482 --> 16:42.264
♪ ♪

16:42.364 --> 16:43.825
- ♪ Mm ♪

16:43.925 --> 16:45.747
♪ So tired ♪

16:45.847 --> 16:48.830
♪ Tired of all this drama ♪

16:48.930 --> 16:50.192
♪ ♪

16:50.292 --> 16:53.275
♪ You go your way,
I go my way ♪

16:53.375 --> 16:54.957
♪ ♪

16:55.057 --> 16:57.639
♪ I need to be free ♪

16:57.739 --> 17:00.162
♪ Broken heart again ♪

17:00.262 --> 17:02.524
♪ Another lesson learned ♪

17:02.624 --> 17:04.967
♪ Better know your friends ♪

17:05.067 --> 17:07.449
♪ Or else you will get burned ♪

17:07.549 --> 17:09.691
♪ Gotta count on me ♪

17:09.791 --> 17:11.814
♪ 'Cause I can guarantee ♪

17:11.914 --> 17:14.216
♪ That I'll be fine ♪

17:14.316 --> 17:15.537
♪ ♪

17:15.637 --> 17:18.781
♪ No more... ♪
chorus: ♪ Pain ♪

17:18.881 --> 17:20.302
- ♪ No more pain ♪

17:20.402 --> 17:22.584
chorus: ♪ No more pain ♪

17:22.684 --> 17:25.187
- ♪ No more pain ♪

17:25.287 --> 17:27.029
chorus: ♪ No drama ♪

17:27.129 --> 17:29.271
- ♪ No more drama in my life ♪

17:29.371 --> 17:30.673
♪ No one's gonna ♪

17:30.773 --> 17:33.676
♪ Make me hurt again ♪

17:33.776 --> 17:36.398
♪ I don't wanna cry no more ♪

17:36.498 --> 17:39.281
♪ Hey, no ♪

17:39.381 --> 17:42.204
♪ I'm so tired
of all the drama! ♪

17:42.304 --> 17:44.326
chorus: ♪ No more drama ♪

17:44.426 --> 17:46.128
- ♪ No! ♪

17:46.228 --> 17:49.051
♪ No, no, never! ♪

17:49.151 --> 17:51.013
♪ Drama ♪

17:51.113 --> 17:52.615
chorus: ♪ No more drama ♪

17:52.715 --> 17:54.897
- ♪ Yeah! ♪

17:54.997 --> 17:58.340
♪ Aw, yeah! ♪

17:58.440 --> 18:00.903
- ♪ I don't want it,
I'm so tired ♪

18:01.003 --> 18:02.384
♪ Of the drama ♪

18:02.484 --> 18:04.346
♪ Go on, get out of my life ♪

18:04.446 --> 18:06.509
♪ My life! ♪

18:06.609 --> 18:09.592
♪ No more drama! ♪

18:09.692 --> 18:12.555
♪ Aah ♪

18:12.655 --> 18:15.197
♪ ♪

18:15.297 --> 18:17.840
♪ Eee, yeah ♪

18:17.940 --> 18:24.787
♪ My life! ♪

18:33.676 --> 18:35.338
- Is there something
you wanna say

18:35.438 --> 18:37.540
that's on your mind?

18:37.640 --> 18:39.982
- Look, Zoey, I love you,

18:40.082 --> 18:42.585
but you rely far too much on me

18:42.685 --> 18:44.347
to do your emotional
heavy lifting,

18:44.447 --> 18:45.908
and it's exhausting.

18:46.008 --> 18:47.710
I mean, it's hard enough for me

18:47.810 --> 18:49.632
to walk around this world
as I am,

18:49.732 --> 18:51.434
and, no,
I'm not about to tell you

18:51.534 --> 18:54.237
how to talk to your
Black friend at work.

18:54.337 --> 18:55.878
So go figure that out
on your own.

18:55.978 --> 18:57.200
- You are right,

18:57.300 --> 18:59.122
and I know Simon,

18:59.222 --> 19:00.523
so I can just be real with him,

19:00.623 --> 19:03.246
and I am gonna go.

19:03.346 --> 19:04.847
[percussive music]

19:04.947 --> 19:07.330
The mural looks...

19:07.430 --> 19:09.052
so good, by the way.

19:09.152 --> 19:12.135
All of you, kudos.

19:12.235 --> 19:14.457
♪ ♪

19:14.557 --> 19:17.340
- Yo, Simon.

19:17.440 --> 19:19.422
What's good, bro?

19:19.522 --> 19:21.104
- Oh, hey, man.
Pretty busy day.

19:21.204 --> 19:22.145
Wish I had more time
to chat, but--

19:22.245 --> 19:23.426
- Oh, for sure.

19:23.526 --> 19:25.268
Look, I just wanted say
how dope it was

19:25.368 --> 19:27.270
to see you speak out like that.

19:27.370 --> 19:29.752
I feel you, bro.

19:29.852 --> 19:31.754
- Do you?

19:31.854 --> 19:33.276
'Cause you seemed
to be really jokey about it

19:33.376 --> 19:35.318
at the town hall.

19:35.418 --> 19:36.519
- Oh, that.

19:36.619 --> 19:38.041
Well, you know,

19:38.141 --> 19:39.722
I'm not really, like,
a "public forum" type of guy,

19:39.822 --> 19:41.044
you know what I'm saying?

19:41.144 --> 19:42.645
I'm more low-key,
but low-key, I got your back.

19:42.745 --> 19:44.167
- Uh-huh.
- Hey.

19:44.267 --> 19:46.009
There you are.
Can we talk?

19:46.109 --> 19:48.111
- Yeah, come on in.

19:49.913 --> 19:50.974
Would you like to know
if I received

19:51.074 --> 19:53.897
your long, very wordy text?

19:53.997 --> 19:55.899
Yes, and thank you.

19:55.999 --> 19:58.381
- It was my 12th attempt.

19:58.481 --> 19:59.663
It sucked.

19:59.763 --> 20:03.667
So, uh...look.

20:03.767 --> 20:05.769
[sighs]

20:06.690 --> 20:09.272
It's really awkward
being the boss sometimes,

20:09.372 --> 20:10.874
but you're also my friend,

20:10.974 --> 20:13.316
so, um...

20:13.416 --> 20:14.838
I'm just gonna be real
with you.

20:14.938 --> 20:16.319
- Okay.

20:16.419 --> 20:18.482
- The board wants you

20:18.582 --> 20:19.923
to retract everything you said

20:20.023 --> 20:21.765
at the press conference.

20:21.865 --> 20:22.966
I know.

20:23.066 --> 20:24.688
It's total BS,

20:24.788 --> 20:27.611
but I'm just the messenger.

20:27.711 --> 20:29.052
But the good news is,

20:29.152 --> 20:30.894
you spoke out,

20:30.994 --> 20:32.656
and you made people aware
of what was happening,

20:32.756 --> 20:33.937
and if you want,

20:34.037 --> 20:35.619
I can even help you write
a revised statement

20:35.719 --> 20:37.180
so you still say something.

20:37.280 --> 20:38.662
Um...

20:38.762 --> 20:40.223
I just want you to know
you're not alone in this.

20:40.323 --> 20:43.347
- Okay, so if we're being real,

20:43.447 --> 20:44.988
I don't feel like
you're just the messenger,

20:45.088 --> 20:49.353
and I do feel
very alone in this.

20:49.453 --> 20:51.635
- I'm on your side.

20:51.735 --> 20:54.398
- It's impossible for you to be
on my side in this situation,

20:54.498 --> 20:57.120
and you cannot
rewrite an experience

20:57.220 --> 20:58.362
you know nothing about.

20:58.462 --> 21:00.604
- I mean,
I know a little, right?

21:00.704 --> 21:01.685
- How?

21:01.785 --> 21:03.207
- I'm a woman
in the tech world!

21:03.307 --> 21:05.249
I know what it's like to be...

21:05.349 --> 21:06.570
- Yes,

21:06.670 --> 21:10.254
but that has nothing to do

21:10.354 --> 21:13.497
with who I am
as a Black man in the world

21:13.597 --> 21:15.339
and what my experience
as a Black man is

21:15.439 --> 21:17.501
in this office.

21:17.601 --> 21:18.742
I never had any mentors

21:18.842 --> 21:20.844
look out for me like Joan.

21:22.085 --> 21:24.668
There's no room
for messing up for me,

21:24.768 --> 21:29.193
and I have to constantly prove
why I deserve to be here.

21:29.293 --> 21:30.874
"Nice office.

21:30.974 --> 21:32.976
How'd you swing that?"

21:35.779 --> 21:36.880
They don't ever ask that

21:36.980 --> 21:38.082
to any of the other
marketing execs.

21:38.182 --> 21:40.444
- You're right.
It's...

21:40.544 --> 21:41.605
That's awful.

21:41.705 --> 21:44.208
- Nah, it's the truth,

21:44.308 --> 21:48.012
and I have to constantly

21:48.112 --> 21:51.015
amputate parts of who I am

21:51.115 --> 21:53.417
to make other people
feel comfortable in my presence

21:53.517 --> 21:54.778
so they feel safe,

21:54.878 --> 21:56.300
so that when I walk
on the elevator,

21:56.400 --> 21:58.542
they--they aren't startled
when they see me.

21:58.642 --> 21:59.743
Do you even have
to think about that?

21:59.843 --> 22:01.585
- I mean...

22:01.685 --> 22:02.827
if I'm being honest,

22:02.927 --> 22:06.070
when I see you,
I just see Simon.

22:06.170 --> 22:08.172
- Simon is a Black man.

22:10.654 --> 22:14.038
You seeing me as only Simon

22:14.138 --> 22:16.140
denies a fundamental part of...

22:17.982 --> 22:20.564
Who I am.

22:20.664 --> 22:23.487
And you asking me

22:23.587 --> 22:28.212
to walk back my words, Zoey,

22:28.312 --> 22:31.335
is telling me to deny that
fundamental part of who I am.

22:31.435 --> 22:34.338
[somber music]

22:34.438 --> 22:36.861
♪ ♪

22:36.961 --> 22:40.264
And whether you're doing that
as my boss or my friend,

22:40.364 --> 22:43.427
that makes you
part of the problem.

22:43.527 --> 22:46.711
So, um,
to answer your question,

22:46.811 --> 22:50.354
no, I will not be retracting
anything that I said.

22:50.454 --> 22:52.356
♪ ♪

22:52.456 --> 22:54.458
Period.

22:58.703 --> 23:00.845
[notifications swooping]
- Hi, Danny.

23:00.945 --> 23:03.728
- So many fires, Zoey.
So many fires.

23:03.828 --> 23:05.530
Why'd you tell me
not to quit again?

23:05.630 --> 23:07.452
- Because you're the leader
of this company,

23:07.552 --> 23:09.654
and you have to do better.

23:09.754 --> 23:11.255
- Oh, we will.
[beeps, dings]

23:11.355 --> 23:13.778
Once we show the world our
patented Sprq Pants technology,

23:13.878 --> 23:15.059
our stock prices will--

23:15.159 --> 23:16.180
- That's not
what I'm talking about.

23:16.280 --> 23:18.343
Can you put away the phone
and the tablet

23:18.443 --> 23:19.624
and the laptop?

23:19.724 --> 23:21.946
- Fine.
- For a second. Please.

23:22.046 --> 23:23.067
[smartwatch buzzing]

23:23.167 --> 23:25.390
- Don't look
at your watch either.

23:25.490 --> 23:27.111
Don't.

23:27.211 --> 23:29.033
I spoke with Simon,

23:29.133 --> 23:31.115
and he's not going
to revise his statement.

23:31.215 --> 23:33.077
I don't blame him,
because the truth is,

23:33.177 --> 23:35.160
I feel like we're
part of the problem,

23:35.260 --> 23:38.243
and he told me
he has felt slighted

23:38.343 --> 23:40.865
and alienated here
for a long time, and...

23:43.588 --> 23:45.290
I can't believe
I've been so oblivious.

23:45.390 --> 23:48.613
- Well, the first step
towards growth is awareness,

23:48.713 --> 23:50.335
so good on you.

23:50.435 --> 23:51.656
Aiden taught me that.

23:51.756 --> 23:54.059
- This is about you, too,

23:54.159 --> 23:56.861
'cause you're the head
of this company.

23:56.961 --> 23:59.104
- Oh, I'm sorry,
did I invent racism?

23:59.204 --> 24:00.986
Or insider trading?

24:01.086 --> 24:02.227
Or trying to create a monopoly?

24:02.327 --> 24:04.109
Or selling thousands of shares
of a company

24:04.209 --> 24:05.510
'cause I knew
it was gonna go down?

24:05.610 --> 24:08.513
I mean, now I'm being
accused of discrimination?

24:08.613 --> 24:10.035
Let's not forget, Zoey,

24:10.135 --> 24:11.957
I am a philanthropist.

24:12.057 --> 24:13.318
[whispers]
I have a foundation.

24:13.418 --> 24:16.521
- And I'm sure that it does
really important work,

24:16.621 --> 24:19.004
but there is a problem

24:19.104 --> 24:21.086
right here at Sprqpoint,

24:21.186 --> 24:23.608
and I think it wouldn't hurt

24:23.708 --> 24:27.292
for both of us
to look at our role in that.

24:27.392 --> 24:28.693
- See, my therapist
actually advised me

24:28.793 --> 24:30.175
not to look inwards anymore.

24:30.275 --> 24:32.417
- I just think that Simon
feels very alone right now,

24:32.517 --> 24:34.219
and the best thing for us to do

24:34.319 --> 24:36.581
would be to stop asking him
to retract his feelings

24:36.681 --> 24:37.863
and instead--
- Zoey.

24:37.963 --> 24:39.825
I can't just march
into a board meeting

24:39.925 --> 24:41.787
and say,
"Oh, one guy's unhappy,

24:41.887 --> 24:43.108
so we need to change
our whole company."

24:43.208 --> 24:44.149
That's not how things work.

24:44.249 --> 24:46.992
- Well, maybe it's time
for things

24:47.092 --> 24:50.716
to start working differently,
then.

24:50.816 --> 24:54.039
I will leave you with that.

24:54.139 --> 24:55.561
I have to get back to work.

24:55.661 --> 24:59.004
- I have to go back to work
here in my office.

24:59.104 --> 25:00.766
♪ ♪

25:00.866 --> 25:03.048
Great, you know what?
87 new messages.

25:03.148 --> 25:04.930
[notification dings]
88.

25:05.030 --> 25:07.032
[notification dings]
No, 89.

25:07.472 --> 25:08.494
- Is it the redirects?

25:08.594 --> 25:09.935
- Checked that already,
Hot Topic.

25:10.035 --> 25:11.016
- What about the database?

25:11.116 --> 25:12.057
- Covered that an hour ago,
Big Bird.

25:12.157 --> 25:13.378
- Man, what are we missing?

25:13.478 --> 25:14.500
- Quality alone time?

25:14.600 --> 25:17.102
- Max, what are you doing here?

25:17.202 --> 25:18.263
- Well, I don't mean
to distract the group,

25:18.363 --> 25:19.344
but Danny told me
to get some help

25:19.444 --> 25:20.786
with a minor coding blip

25:20.886 --> 25:23.188
after saying he was all in.
- Mm.

25:23.288 --> 25:25.471
Mo told me.
Congrats.

25:25.571 --> 25:27.753
- Thank you.
- I like seeing you here.

25:27.853 --> 25:30.676
It almost makes me not wanna go
hide in an isolation pod.

25:30.776 --> 25:32.277
- I got it, I got it,
I got it, I got it, I got it.

25:32.377 --> 25:34.079
You're making all the API
requests at the same time,

25:34.179 --> 25:36.402
so what if we do a sync process
and cache the results?

25:36.502 --> 25:39.485
- Hold on a second.
That might actually work.

25:39.585 --> 25:40.726
You know, I never thought
I'd say this,

25:40.826 --> 25:42.888
but thank you, Tobin.

25:42.988 --> 25:44.730
- It's a good thing
we outsourced it to Slumdog.

25:44.830 --> 25:46.131
