♪ ♪

27:10.596 --> 27:15.622
♪ The tracks of my tears ♪

27:15.722 --> 27:20.606
♪ ♪

27:22.528 --> 27:23.830
- Tobin.

27:23.930 --> 27:25.271
Can we chat for a sec?

27:25.371 --> 27:27.594
- Uh-oh, pray for me,
everybody.

27:27.694 --> 27:29.796
[laughter]

27:29.896 --> 27:31.998
- Hey, I just wanna
say thank you

27:32.098 --> 27:33.359
for helping me today.

27:33.459 --> 27:35.522
It feels great to be around
like minds again.

27:35.622 --> 27:37.884
I forgot how much
I missed the comradery,

27:37.984 --> 27:40.166
and Mackenzie,

27:40.266 --> 27:43.810
I feel both flattered
and objectified.

27:43.910 --> 27:46.973
Anyway, I'm gonna add
a special Sprqpoint discount

27:47.073 --> 27:48.735
for you all to use
anytime you want.

27:48.835 --> 27:51.438
Except for you, Leif.
You have to pay full price.

27:52.238 --> 27:54.501
- Hey, if this is about
the burn spot on the ceiling,

27:54.601 --> 27:55.982
it I was a trick
I saw Criss Angel do,

27:56.082 --> 27:57.784
and Mackenzie dared me,
so I had to.

27:57.884 --> 27:59.546
- What? Really?

27:59.646 --> 28:01.067
Where?

28:01.167 --> 28:02.829
I really just wanted to, um,

28:02.929 --> 28:05.792
check in, see how you're doing.

28:05.892 --> 28:07.234
- Obviously, you saw me
crushing it out there,

28:07.334 --> 28:09.316
so doing great.

28:09.416 --> 28:10.397
- Yeah, that was amazing.

28:10.497 --> 28:13.300
Um, what I mean is, um...

28:15.982 --> 28:18.124
How do you feel
about Simon's press conference

28:18.224 --> 28:19.166
and everything he said?

28:19.266 --> 28:20.967
Did that stir up anything

28:21.067 --> 28:23.250
particular for you?

28:23.350 --> 28:25.051
- Yeah, it made me think
of all the tough questions:

28:25.151 --> 28:27.094
racial equality,
corporate bias,

28:27.194 --> 28:29.336
why does Simon look
so damn good in a suit?

28:29.436 --> 28:31.218
- I just, um,

28:31.318 --> 28:33.500
I feel like...

28:33.600 --> 28:36.943
you might be kind of hurt
or upset.

28:37.043 --> 28:39.987
I mean, it must be tough

28:40.087 --> 28:41.308
making yourself
the butt of the joke.

28:41.408 --> 28:42.909
- Not really.

28:43.009 --> 28:44.831
I mean, most humor
comes from personal experience.

28:44.931 --> 28:47.434
At least that's what me
and Dave Chappelle believe.

28:47.534 --> 28:48.915
- Okay, but is it worth it?

28:49.015 --> 28:51.038
I mean, putting yourself
out there all the time

28:51.138 --> 28:53.580
for other people's amusement.
I just...

28:55.983 --> 28:57.985
I feel like you're
really good at deflecting.

28:58.665 --> 29:00.287
- Okay, well, thank you
for the analysis, Dr. Clarke.

29:00.387 --> 29:01.368
Uh, may I leave now?

29:01.468 --> 29:03.470
- Okay.

29:11.038 --> 29:12.940
- You wanna know why
I make jokes all the time?

29:13.040 --> 29:15.142
It's because I'm a first-gen.
It's how I fit in.

29:15.242 --> 29:16.663
It's how I've always fit in

29:16.763 --> 29:18.145
because I don't really
fit in anywhere.

29:18.245 --> 29:19.386
- Even here?

29:19.486 --> 29:21.308
- At Sprqpoint?
Are you kidding me?

29:21.408 --> 29:23.150
You know how shocked people
in other departments are

29:23.250 --> 29:24.591
when they meet me
and I don't have an accent

29:24.691 --> 29:26.473
or I'm not the guy
delivering their shawarma?

29:26.573 --> 29:27.755
Happens all the time.

29:27.855 --> 29:30.177
- No one should have
to feel this way at work.

29:32.139 --> 29:33.200
You should say something.

29:33.300 --> 29:34.521
- To who?
HR?

29:34.621 --> 29:36.163
Danny Michael Davis?
What am I gonna say?

29:36.263 --> 29:37.564
"People are treating me
like an Indian guy."

29:37.664 --> 29:39.046
Guess what, Zoey.
I'm an Indian guy.

29:39.146 --> 29:40.848
- The company is asking Simon

29:40.948 --> 29:43.450
to say that he's the only one
who feels this way.

29:43.550 --> 29:45.773
He clearly isn't.

29:45.873 --> 29:47.374
You could help him.

29:47.474 --> 29:49.096
You could help other people

29:49.196 --> 29:52.099
that maybe feel similar
as you and Simon.

29:52.199 --> 29:54.381
- I respect Simon for
speaking out, I do, I just...

29:54.481 --> 29:56.944
[somber music]

29:57.044 --> 29:58.425
I don't wanna stir the pot.

29:58.525 --> 30:00.267
- Okay.

30:00.367 --> 30:01.228
But what if--
- No.

30:01.328 --> 30:02.790
If you need help
with a coding glitch

30:02.890 --> 30:05.352
or a charmingly offensive pun,
I'm all over it,

30:05.452 --> 30:07.274
but this...

30:07.374 --> 30:09.076
I'm sorry, I can't.

30:09.176 --> 30:10.958
♪ ♪

30:11.058 --> 30:12.520
I'm sorry.

30:12.620 --> 30:17.865
♪ ♪

30:22.029 --> 30:24.251
- All right, so I know
exactly how this goes.

30:24.351 --> 30:25.773
If I don't retract
my statement,

30:25.873 --> 30:28.296
they'll slowly,
methodically ice me out.

30:28.396 --> 30:30.898
In a few months,
there'll be a new head of PR.

30:30.998 --> 30:32.580
My white bosses
will give me a promotion

30:32.680 --> 30:34.422
to some new job
no one's ever heard of

30:34.522 --> 30:37.505
where I'll have
no opportunity to rise

30:37.605 --> 30:39.227
and no voice, period.

30:39.327 --> 30:40.628
- Mm.

30:40.728 --> 30:42.750
I just had a vision
of me without a voice.

30:42.850 --> 30:44.712
I don't like it.

30:44.812 --> 30:46.794
- Received.
- Mm.

30:46.894 --> 30:49.417
- [sighs]

30:51.459 --> 30:53.281
Okay, so maybe I should

30:53.381 --> 30:55.983
just retract everything I said.

30:56.864 --> 31:00.007
Just keep my head down,

31:00.107 --> 31:02.110
stack my checks.

31:03.391 --> 31:05.533
I mean, who was I to think that
I could change any of this?

31:05.633 --> 31:07.635
- Listen to me.
- [sighs]

31:09.557 --> 31:11.959
- You are a gorgeous
Black man...

31:13.961 --> 31:16.464
With a big heart,

31:16.564 --> 31:19.107
and you shouldn't have to put
your head down anywhere,

31:19.207 --> 31:21.109
and if you can't
be your whole self there,

31:21.209 --> 31:22.110
then they don't deserve you.

31:22.210 --> 31:23.031
Do you hear me?

31:23.131 --> 31:25.133
- Yeah.

31:26.414 --> 31:27.715
You're right.

31:27.815 --> 31:29.077
- So what you gonna
do about it?

31:29.177 --> 31:31.179
- Hey.

31:42.710 --> 31:45.774
I don't want to interrupt,
but I do want to apologize.

31:45.874 --> 31:47.736
Clearly, I have blind spots,

31:47.836 --> 31:49.217
and I'm embarrassed
that you guys

31:49.317 --> 31:50.498
had to be the ones
to point that out,

31:50.598 --> 31:53.361
so I just--
I'm really sorry.

31:55.083 --> 31:57.025
Good night.

31:57.125 --> 31:58.426
- Zoey, wait.

31:58.526 --> 32:01.129
I decided that I...

32:04.612 --> 32:05.794
I'm going in
first thing tomorrow

32:05.894 --> 32:07.896
and telling Danny that I quit.

32:11.099 --> 32:13.101
- Okay.

32:15.023 --> 32:16.284
- "Okay"?
Wait, wait.

32:16.384 --> 32:18.206
That's--that's it?

32:18.306 --> 32:19.848
You're not gonna make
some big speech

32:19.948 --> 32:23.452
and tell me I shouldn't do it?

32:23.552 --> 32:25.534
- No.

32:25.634 --> 32:28.597
You have to do what feels
right for you, and...

32:30.879 --> 32:33.401
I support you.

32:34.763 --> 32:37.305
[door clicks open]

32:37.405 --> 32:39.348
[elevator dings]

32:39.448 --> 32:42.311
[somber music]

32:42.411 --> 32:49.297
♪ ♪

32:51.980 --> 32:54.643
- Wow, this is crazy.
- What?

32:54.743 --> 32:56.725
Did another one of our products
burst into flames?

32:56.825 --> 32:58.327
- No, check this out.

32:58.427 --> 33:04.092
♪ ♪

33:04.192 --> 33:06.194
- Oh, my God.

33:07.556 --> 33:09.138
[laughs]

33:09.238 --> 33:10.699
I can't believe this.

33:10.799 --> 33:12.181
- Are you gonna--

33:12.281 --> 33:14.463
all right, I'll just grab
my phone from you later.

33:14.563 --> 33:17.426
[uplifting music]

33:17.526 --> 33:19.068
♪ ♪

33:19.168 --> 33:20.989
- Tobin, you did it.

33:21.089 --> 33:23.632
You!

33:23.732 --> 33:25.074
You spoke out!

33:25.174 --> 33:27.116
- I did.
Um, thank you.

33:27.216 --> 33:29.638
- This is huge.

33:29.738 --> 33:31.280
What changed your mind?

33:31.380 --> 33:32.801
- I mean,
I wasn't gonna say anything,

33:32.901 --> 33:35.444
but I thought a lot
about our convo,

33:35.544 --> 33:37.446
and after a couple
of "Queer Eye" episodes

33:37.546 --> 33:40.849
and a Negroni nightcap,
I was feeling pretty raw,

33:40.949 --> 33:43.212
so I decided to just speak up,
put it all out there,

33:43.312 --> 33:44.573
consequences be damned,

33:44.673 --> 33:46.455
but I had no idea the hashtag
#BIPOCAtSprqpoint

33:46.555 --> 33:47.897
was gonna blow up like that.

33:47.997 --> 33:49.378
- I mean, there must
be hundreds of posts in here.

33:49.478 --> 33:50.940
- Including a few
supportive Sprqpoint hotties

33:51.040 --> 33:52.621
who slid into my DMs.

33:52.721 --> 33:53.903
Happy accident.
Not my intention.

33:54.003 --> 33:55.784
- Wait.

33:55.884 --> 33:58.147
Simon is in Danny Michael
Davis's office quitting

33:58.247 --> 33:59.528
because he thinks he's
the only person at Sprqpoint

33:59.608 --> 34:00.509
who feels this way.

34:00.609 --> 34:01.751
They need to see this now.

34:01.851 --> 34:03.232
- Totally.

34:03.332 --> 34:05.234
Let me just respond
to this DM really quick.

34:05.334 --> 34:07.436
"I know,
discrimination is the worst."

34:07.536 --> 34:08.998
- Tobin.

34:09.098 --> 34:11.921
- "Wanna grab coffee?"
All right, let's go.

34:12.021 --> 34:13.322
- One of my favorite--
- Simon, hold up!

34:13.422 --> 34:15.044
- Okay, okay, take a breath.

34:15.144 --> 34:17.146
You're sweating
through your sweater.

34:18.467 --> 34:20.770
- Okay, um, listen.

34:20.870 --> 34:23.372
Tobin posted about
his experience online,

34:23.472 --> 34:27.456
and now there are literally
hundreds of Sprqpoint employees

34:27.556 --> 34:28.698
who are sharing
their own stories.

34:28.798 --> 34:30.259
- Not the way your boy expected
to blow up online,

34:30.359 --> 34:31.621
but I'll take it.

34:31.721 --> 34:32.942
- And these stories
aren't just from here.

34:33.042 --> 34:35.304
They're from Sprqpoint offices
all over the world.

34:35.404 --> 34:38.067
London, Hong Kong, Reykjavik--

34:38.167 --> 34:39.669
I didn't even know that
we had an office in Reykjavik!

34:39.769 --> 34:41.771
- Okay, sit down.

34:42.091 --> 34:43.392
[sighs]
First of all,

34:43.492 --> 34:46.235
I'm right here,
and you're screaming, kay?

34:46.335 --> 34:48.678
Mm.
Also, I have the internet too.

34:48.778 --> 34:50.159
I saw the posts.

34:50.259 --> 34:51.721
- Yeah, we've been
going through them together.

34:51.821 --> 34:53.823
- Oh.

34:54.824 --> 34:56.085
Well, good!

34:56.185 --> 34:57.527
I mean,
this changes everything, right?

34:57.627 --> 34:58.728
It's fantastic news.

34:58.828 --> 35:00.370
I mean, terrible
and deeply worrisome

35:00.470 --> 35:02.972
that this even exists, but--
- Clearly I'm not alone here.

35:03.072 --> 35:04.934
- No, that's true, and look,

35:05.034 --> 35:07.316
I can't believe this all
happened under my roofs.

35:08.678 --> 35:11.741
But armed with these stories,

35:11.841 --> 35:13.343
I'm going to walk
into that board room,

35:13.443 --> 35:14.544
and I'm going to demand

35:14.644 --> 35:17.947
real and lasting changes
around here,

35:18.047 --> 35:19.869
because, damn it,
that's what a hero does.

35:19.969 --> 35:21.110
- Uh-uh, you're not the hero
in this situation.

35:21.210 --> 35:22.131
- You still got a lot
of work to do, man.

35:22.211 --> 35:24.434
- But the agenda

35:24.534 --> 35:26.356
for today's board meeting

35:26.456 --> 35:28.458
has officially been amended.

35:29.299 --> 35:30.760
You guys just get the chills?

35:30.860 --> 35:31.661
- Not even a little bit.
- Not a bit.

35:31.741 --> 35:33.743
- Maybe a little.

35:34.584 --> 35:36.586
What?

35:38.428 --> 35:39.689
- As you all know,

35:39.789 --> 35:40.810
we're here to discuss

35:40.910 --> 35:41.891
our course of action

35:41.991 --> 35:43.613
based on the recent claims

35:43.713 --> 35:45.655
made by our employee,
Simon Haynes,

35:45.755 --> 35:47.257
but it has come to my attention

35:47.357 --> 35:49.659
that, um, I might not know

35:49.759 --> 35:51.261
what the hell
I'm talking about,

35:51.361 --> 35:53.343
so I have invited

35:53.443 --> 35:56.486
someone far more qualified
to speak on this.

36:03.373 --> 36:05.035
[somber music]

36:05.135 --> 36:06.316
- [sighs]

36:06.416 --> 36:08.278
Ladies and gentlemen
of the board,

36:08.378 --> 36:10.360
I--I would, indeed,

36:10.460 --> 36:12.762
like to clarify my words
from the other day

36:12.862 --> 36:16.766
and get more specific
about the racism

36:16.866 --> 36:19.489
that exists within Sprqpoint,

36:19.589 --> 36:20.931
and I'll also
be revising my statement

36:21.031 --> 36:23.693
and saying that it is not
just my experience.

36:23.793 --> 36:27.617
♪ ♪

36:27.717 --> 36:30.100
A Black executive in New York

36:30.200 --> 36:31.782
was working late one night

36:31.882 --> 36:35.145
and was profiled at his
own desk by a security guard,

36:35.245 --> 36:37.748
a receptionist in London
was let go and then told

36:37.848 --> 36:39.549
it was because her locks
looked unprofessional,

36:39.649 --> 36:41.351
and here, in this very office,

36:41.451 --> 36:44.434
an intern quit
because her boss joked

36:44.534 --> 36:45.716
that if she were to ever
come in late,

36:45.816 --> 36:49.079
he would call ICE.

36:49.179 --> 36:50.721
See, we're not gonna
be able to fix this problem

36:50.821 --> 36:55.005
with just diversity committees,

36:55.105 --> 36:57.487
workshops,

36:57.587 --> 36:59.850
donating to a few places
to help clear your conscious.

36:59.950 --> 37:03.894
It's about changing
the culture here.

37:03.994 --> 37:06.577
It's about being inclusive
in the rooms

37:06.677 --> 37:08.679
where decisions
are being made...

37:10.520 --> 37:11.942
Including this one.

